1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,500
All characters, behaviors, places, occupations, and events in this series are fictional and created for entertainment purposes.

2
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:15,000
There is no intention to promote any actions depicted. Viewer discretion is advised.

3
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:24,400
Respected Members of the board and all employees of MAIO Corporation,

4
00:00:24,620 --> 00:00:28,680
before we begin the annual meeting today,

5
00:00:28,860 --> 00:00:30,700
I would like to inform you all

6
00:00:30,860 --> 00:00:35,180
of an important announcement from Mrs. Pimpan Prasertrungruangtham.

7
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:40,160
It’s wonderful and important news that she would like to share herself.

8
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,120
Please welcome her on stage.

9
00:00:50,140 --> 00:00:52,120
Hello, everyone.

10
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:55,260
I'll keep it brief today.

11
00:00:55,260 --> 00:00:57,500
For the past ten years,

12
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:03,740
continuing my husband's legacy in managing this company

13
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:08,560
has been very tough for someone my age.

14
00:01:10,060 --> 00:01:11,260
Today,

15
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:15,920
I’m going to pass the company down to my grandson.

16
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:21,260
And that person is...

17
00:01:21,660 --> 00:01:25,360
Parinth Prasertrungruangtham.

18
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:27,800
Mr. Parinth!

19
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,600
Where is he?

20
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,440
Madam has a grandson?

21
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:12,220
You know nothing. Mr. Parinth is her beloved grandson.

22
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,940
He's just graduated from abroad.

23
00:02:13,940 --> 00:02:16,480
He's handsome and rich.

24
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,540
What a perfect man!

25
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:22,140
Is this really the time for jokes?

26
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,480
You want a grand opening, don't you?

27
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:29,860
I am confident

28
00:02:30,740 --> 00:02:36,600
that Parinth will take the company to new heights.

29
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:43,600
I hope that everyone will continue to work hard just like you always have.

30
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:56,100
Also,

31
00:02:57,060 --> 00:02:59,920
there's one more thing I would like to inform you all.

32
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:01,940
What is it?

33
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,700
My grandson...

34
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,900
is still single and ready to mingle.

35
00:03:25,780 --> 00:03:28,400
(1 Year Later)

36
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:31,520
About the interview session with your new secretary.

37
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:32,400
What about it?

38
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:35,340
Our HR will interview the candidates today,

39
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:37,340
and they can likely start working tomorrow.

40
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,860
What am I supposed to do if you all work so slowly?

41
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:41,980
I'm sorry, boss.

42
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:45,720
I'm so sorry, Mr. Parinth.

43
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:47,600
Whatever.

44
00:03:51,580 --> 00:03:52,960
Brace yourself.

45
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:56,340
Three, two, one.

46
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:59,480
Gosh! I was so tense!

47
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:02,000
You're lucky that he didn't scold you.

48
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:06,080
I bet he already did.

49
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,660
Handsome, rich, and perfect? I don't want any of that!

50
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,100
He can't even be friendly with his employees.

51
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:15,880
It's okay, sis.

52
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:18,520
Eat this to help calm yourself down.

53
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:22,940
Calm down, sis.

54
00:04:24,380 --> 00:04:26,120
Auntie, be careful!

55
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:29,940
The water is spilled. Please clean it up.

56
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,420
Sis, so your feelings have changed?

57
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,580
You don't like him anymore?

58
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:36,300
I was just excited in the beginning.

59
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:39,780
How can I like my own boss? No way! That’s just crazy!

60
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,380
Does he even like girls?

61
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:46,740
Maybe he just doesn't like anyone.

62
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:51,080
You have to think about those who don't need love in life.

63
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:53,180
Whatever.

64
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:56,100
I have Gong Yoo as my husband, and that's more than enough.

65
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:59,000
Do you think he wants you?

66
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:02,860
Sis, even he knows you're being delusional.

67
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,820
How can he change his secretary every day?

68
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:25,580
It's been a year already, and he is still not getting along with his employees.

69
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:36,040
Auntie.

70
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,160
Auntie.

71
00:05:38,460 --> 00:05:39,460
Are you okay?

72
00:05:40,780 --> 00:05:41,500
Auntie.

73
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:42,520
Breathe.

74
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:43,680
Please help!

75
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:45,460
Someone is fainting. Please help!

76
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,720
Auntie, breathe.

77
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,380
Grandma!

78
00:05:51,130 --> 00:05:54,260
Oh, you're here.

79
00:05:55,440 --> 00:06:00,760
I thought I wouldn't wake up to see my dear grandson.

80
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:07,520
I admit that I'm getting old.

81
00:06:11,530 --> 00:06:14,200
I feel like I might die just from falling.

82
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:19,640
Your grandpa likes to come into my dreams.

83
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:24,060
It’s like he wants to take me to be with him.

84
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:25,480
Grandma.

85
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,700
Don't think too much.

86
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,400
Get some rest.

87
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:37,060
Nanon.

88
00:06:37,780 --> 00:06:39,320
Why haven't you changed my grandma's shoes yet?

89
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,000
Oh.

90
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,340
I already changed to orthopedic shoes for her.

91
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:44,600
But she wanted to wear high heels.

92
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:49,400
Well, um, the shoes look pretty ugly.

93
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:53,200
I just want to wear something nice.

94
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,040
How can it be ugly?

95
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,240
I bought you only good things,

96
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:59,520
and this pair of shoes is the most popular.

97
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:01,980
Please be careful when you walk.

98
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:03,220
You're already old.

99
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:05,100
It's easy to fall down.

100
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:09,540
Gosh! You keep calling me old.

101
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:13,040
I'm not old. I'm just classic!

102
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:16,400
It still means old.

103
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,900
Parinth.

104
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,720
I'm serious this time.

105
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:27,440
Can you date someone for me?

106
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:33,420
Grandma.

107
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:38,740
It can be a girl or a boy.

108
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:40,480
I don't mind.

109
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:45,760
Mabel asked me to watch the BL series with her.

110
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,580
I like it!

111
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:49,520
It's cute.

112
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:50,320
That's right!

113
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:53,320
Whoever doesn't like it, that's up to them.

114
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,300
I can accept it.

115
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:03,720
If there's anything that can make you happy,

116
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,280
I can accept it all.

117
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,160
I'm happy...

118
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:17,900
when I work.

119
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:20,040
Please let me work.

120
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:23,780
Nanon, Mabel.

121
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:24,620
Yes, sir.

122
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,060
Take care of grandma for me.

123
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,240
Don't let her out of sight.

124
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:34,940
The older she gets, the more stubborn she becomes.

125
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:38,200
No! She's not stubborn at all.

126
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,720
I always keep an eye on her, and Nanon is helping me too.

127
00:08:43,460 --> 00:08:45,080
Can I trust you guys?

128
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,340
Think you're so good, huh?

129
00:09:05,370 --> 00:09:06,580
Hello, Mr. Parinth.

130
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:07,700
I'm...

131
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:10,740
I'm First Ekdanai.

132
00:09:11,140 --> 00:09:12,660
I will be your secretary.

133
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,760
Um.

134
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:21,700
Follow me.

135
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:39,940
This is your tablet.

136
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:43,320
You can jot down my schedule here.

137
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:44,800
It's synced with my tablet.

138
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,300
One more thing.

139
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:50,360
I want you to remind me about the meeting

140
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:51,800
one day before

141
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,880
and one hour before the scheduled time.

142
00:09:54,420 --> 00:09:55,480
Do you understand?

143
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:57,560
Yes.

144
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,320
But...

145
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:02,540
I'm more used to writing with pen.

146
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:09,420
Do you know what our company does?

147
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:12,200
Yes.

148
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:13,660
You know, right?

149
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:14,840
Yes, I do.

150
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:32,180
Right now, I'm in the process of rebranding the company.

151
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:34,140
The brand was founded in my grandpa's generation.

152
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:38,580
My team has finished the analysis and updated all products.

153
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:43,500
The next step is to find a marketing agency to advertise our company.

154
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:45,280
Hey!

155
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,940
Can you keep up?

156
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:48,820
Yes.

157
00:10:48,880 --> 00:10:49,460
I can keep up.

158
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:16,720
I'm so sorry!

159
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,840
From now on, learn how to use the tablet.

160
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,640
Yes, sir.

161
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,720
How about this?

162
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:45,180
I’ll give you your first task.

163
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:49,540
Find me ten marketing agencies to choose from

164
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:50,840
by tomorrow.

165
00:11:53,420 --> 00:11:54,240
How many agencies again?

166
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,220
Ten agencies.

167
00:11:55,420 --> 00:11:56,720
Ten agencies!

168
00:11:58,720 --> 00:11:59,940
By tomorrow?

169
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,320
You can go now.

170
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,500
I have a meeting.

171
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,500
Can he manage?

172
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:23,740
He's here.

173
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:42,720
You're not going, sis?

174
00:12:44,580 --> 00:12:46,020
- Goodbye.
- Good luck.

175
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:28,060
Mr. Parinth, I have sent you the file containing information on the ten agencies

176
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:30,060
attending the meeting tomorrow.

177
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:32,900
The meeting schedule is also included in the file.

178
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,720
Thank you, First.

179
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:53,140
Here's the marketing plan that I came up with.

180
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:56,700
Mr. Parinth, I would like to thank you for giving me this opportunity.

181
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:59,200
My family really likes your product.

182
00:13:59,260 --> 00:14:03,440
Hello, Mr. Parinth. I'm so glad that your company contacted me.

183
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,780
We really look up to your company.

184
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:09,860
I was so excited when I heard about the rebranding of your brand!

185
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:13,980
I also heard that you graduated with an MBA from abroad, right?

186
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:18,140
We can also reach other target audience groups.

187
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:22,960
Mr. Parinth, are you interested in having lunch with me?

188
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,520
How was it today?

189
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:36,500
I'm sorry that I could only make appointments with five agencies.

190
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,800
The rest would like to reschedule.

191
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:46,060
I'm not interested in any of them yet.

192
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:48,660
Make appointments with the remaining seven agencies tomorrow.

193
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:53,720
Okay.

194
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,080
Noted.

195
00:15:04,180 --> 00:15:05,780
I told you to use the tablet!

196
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,120
I'm sorry.

197
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:10,640
Get out.

198
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:19,600
Will he be able to manage this?

199
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:34,980
Mr. Parinth, do you have a specific topic you want them to present?

200
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:44,380
I want to see case studies that show me a better picture.

201
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:45,660
Copy that.

202
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,180
Do you want the presentation in English or Thai?

203
00:15:57,260 --> 00:15:59,320
Do you have the limit number of slides?

204
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:01,920
Do you want them to present the case study using graphs or infographics?

205
00:16:01,980 --> 00:16:04,580
Do you want only the case study from Thailand?

206
00:16:04,660 --> 00:16:07,240
Do you want them to focus on any particular product?

207
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:11,460
You can decide. I'll look at it tomorrow.

208
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:26,600
I've already made appointments with three agencies for tomorrow.

209
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,220
I'll send you the details.

210
00:16:31,540 --> 00:16:32,640
Just three?

211
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:36,380
How come only three appointments?

212
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:39,100
That's right, sir.

213
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:46,600
I also designed a new logo that is more modern and minimal to appeal to all age groups.

214
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:49,860
I want you to take a look, and you can make a decision later.

215
00:16:50,210 --> 00:16:56,420
I think we shouldn't overlook customer loyalty.

216
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:59,120
Based on my research with the focus group.

217
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:00,140
You can see right here.

218
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:03,520
The users are really satisfied with your brand

219
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:07,960
compared to other brands offering the same product.

220
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,480
These customers come back to buy the product again.

221
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:19,100
How was it today, Mr. Parinth?

222
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,760
Why did you make only three appointments?

223
00:17:22,660 --> 00:17:23,720
Are you already burnt out?

224
00:17:25,360 --> 00:17:26,220
No.

225
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:28,220
Actually, there are more.

226
00:17:28,660 --> 00:17:34,080
But I saw that you were so tired after five meetings yesterday.

227
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:37,960
I think three agencies would be just right.

228
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:49,140
I printed out my notes from all the meetings today.

229
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,020
Alright.

230
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:04,500
You did a good job today.

231
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:30,440
DNA agency seems to have a good vision.

232
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:33,260
But their marketing plan is too unrealistic.

233
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:37,220
2Four Agency is average.

234
00:18:37,340 --> 00:18:39,480
Their data seems to come from the internet.

235
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:41,100
They’re not experts in this.

236
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:45,660
CIC Agency has a good plan.

237
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:47,580
But the speaker couldn't stay still.

238
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,520
He was either too nervous or really needed to go to the toilet.

239
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:54,100
Be Trendy Agency has a really nice presentation.

240
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:56,220
But the speaker couldn't pronouce the words properly.

241
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,420
This will make Mr. Parinth angry if we work together.

242
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:34,460
First.

243
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:47,200
How did your Gong Yoo's series end?

244
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:50,460
It was so good that I even dreamt about it.

245
00:19:50,620 --> 00:19:51,720
How good was it?

246
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,500
It was such a sweet dream!

247
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,300
Hello, boss.

248
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:07,340
Here it is.

249
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:11,340
- I bought you guys coffee.
- Oh, you're finally here.

250
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,200
Hot coffee for you.

251
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,600
There you go.

252
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:17,080
- This is your iced latte.
- Thank you.

253
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:19,340
- You're the kindest!
- You're welcome.

254
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:22,200
This one is yours!

255
00:20:22,660 --> 00:20:23,940
Hello, Mr. Parinth.

256
00:20:25,980 --> 00:20:27,120
Where's my coffee?

257
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:31,420
You didn't order it, did you?

258
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,480
You're my secretary, right?

259
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:35,800
Yes.

260
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,140
I'm your boss, right?

261
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:39,480
Yes.

262
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:41,980
But you bought coffee for everyone except me.

263
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:47,240
Oh, Mr. Parinth!

264
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:52,920
If I buy it for you and you don't like it, you’ll scold me again.

265
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:53,860
First!

266
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:54,740
Yes.

267
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:57,880
I'll go buy it for you now.

268
00:20:57,940 --> 00:20:58,760
No need.

269
00:21:04,660 --> 00:21:05,900
I'll buy it myself.

270
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:09,920
Oh, okay.

271
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,620
I said I'll buy it myself.

272
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:21,420
Oh! I'll go with you.

273
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:33,680
Iced Americano with no ice, please.

274
00:21:35,980 --> 00:21:36,840
Mr. Parinth.

275
