476
00:39:59,540 --> 00:40:02,360
You know when he's angry,

477
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:04,260
it's really hard to please him.

478
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:06,380
Umm.

479
00:40:08,180 --> 00:40:09,660
He seems arrogant.

480
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:11,140
You think so?

481
00:40:12,940 --> 00:40:15,180
- But boss--
- That's not true!

482
00:40:15,300 --> 00:40:16,940
Mr. Parinth is not like that.

483
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:19,620
Oh, First.

484
00:40:20,020 --> 00:40:22,080
Well, First....

485
00:40:22,560 --> 00:40:26,700
- We're just talking.
- Yes, just like the usual.

486
00:40:26,940 --> 00:40:28,320
Don't mind us.

487
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:34,160
I think Mr. Parinth just takes his work seriously.

488
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:36,160
Also, he's not an arrogant person.

489
00:40:36,900 --> 00:40:39,160
I see. He's just serious about work.

490
00:40:39,160 --> 00:40:41,220
He only wants this company to thrive forward.

491
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:43,280
He doesn't have any bad intention.

492
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,120
Ah, I understand now.

493
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:47,600
You're right. I agree with you.

494
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,280
Thank you, Mr. Parinth,

495
00:41:03,020 --> 00:41:04,440
for lending me your clothes.

496
00:41:11,540 --> 00:41:15,580
I don't know where to start too.

497
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:23,080
But I want you to try first.

498
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:24,760
Try what?

499
00:41:26,700 --> 00:41:29,520
You can try eating out with others.

500
00:41:30,380 --> 00:41:32,240
Try to socialize more.

501
00:41:32,340 --> 00:41:33,960
It's not that hard.

502
00:41:34,100 --> 00:41:36,420
But I understand that there's always a first time for everything.

503
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:44,180
What do you think they want to eat?

504
00:41:47,580 --> 00:41:48,560
Everyone,

505
00:41:49,380 --> 00:41:50,760
I bought some snacks for you all.

506
00:41:53,500 --> 00:41:54,960
Feel free to eat.

507
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:57,700
Wow! We're already hungry.

508
00:41:57,700 --> 00:42:01,920
These are all my favorites! I will eat them all.

509
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:04,800
What, sis? You just said you're on diet.

510
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:09,600
Mr. Parinth.

511
00:42:10,340 --> 00:42:11,740
Who is this client?

512
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:14,260
Why did you come to meet her personally?

513
00:42:14,580 --> 00:42:15,400
Oh.

514
00:42:15,940 --> 00:42:17,500
She’s my friend from when I studied abroad.

515
00:42:18,740 --> 00:42:19,740
Por!

516
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:22,880
Lin!

517
00:42:23,060 --> 00:42:24,300
Oh my!

518
00:42:24,560 --> 00:42:25,980
You look dashing!

519
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,580
I miss you so much! Long time no see.

520
00:42:30,580 --> 00:42:31,360
I miss you too.

521
00:42:31,900 --> 00:42:32,980
Let's take a seat first.

522
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:35,660
I'm so happy to see you.

523
00:42:36,060 --> 00:42:38,640
You’re always busy, so I don’t dare to reach out.

524
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:41,300
You're the busy one, not me.

525
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:44,420
And this is?

526
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:47,020
Oh.

527
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:49,080
He's my secretary. His name is First.

528
00:42:49,080 --> 00:42:50,500
I see.

529
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:52,080
Hello.

530
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:55,280
Nice to meet you. I'm Pailin.

531
00:42:55,660 --> 00:42:57,560
Por is always grumpy.

532
00:42:57,720 --> 00:42:58,640
Please bear with him.

533
00:42:58,700 --> 00:42:59,060
Hey!

534
00:42:59,620 --> 00:43:00,780
You chew me out again.

535
00:43:00,780 --> 00:43:02,780
You see? He's nagging again.

536
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:08,760
It's the truth. You always change your secretary.

537
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:10,180
That's not true.

538
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:10,920
Yes, it is!

539
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:12,240
You're exaggerating.

540
00:43:12,240 --> 00:43:13,580
I'm not!

541
00:43:13,580 --> 00:43:14,620
Fine, you win.

542
00:43:14,700 --> 00:43:16,660
How's your company?

543
00:43:17,700 --> 00:43:23,680
We're mainly exporting products and expanding our market to the Latin American region.

544
00:43:23,900 --> 00:43:25,080
I'm quite busy these days.

545
00:43:25,140 --> 00:43:26,160
I see.

546
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:31,400
You were busy back then, and you're even busier now.

547
00:43:31,760 --> 00:43:34,700
That's not it. I'm currently learning Spanish.

548
00:43:35,540 --> 00:43:36,900
- Really?
- Yes.

549
00:43:36,940 --> 00:43:37,660
You're amazing.

550
00:43:37,840 --> 00:43:40,000
I want to be as good as you.

551
00:43:44,060 --> 00:43:45,620
I'll go order you a coffee.

552
00:43:47,180 --> 00:43:50,040
Iced Americano with no ice, right?

553
00:43:51,340 --> 00:43:52,260
You know me.

554
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:55,920
You don't have to go, First. It's embarrassing.

555
00:43:56,060 --> 00:43:57,780
Let him go order it by himself.

556
00:43:59,060 --> 00:44:00,020
How can it be embarrassing?

557
00:44:00,660 --> 00:44:03,700
It is! Who in the world drinks such a thing?

558
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:04,920
I do!

559
00:44:05,100 --> 00:44:06,100
That's why you're weird.

560
00:44:07,600 --> 00:44:08,840
I'll go order it then.

561
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:12,960
Who drinks it without ice?

562
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:13,720
I like it!

563
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:19,160
Iced Americano...

564
00:44:20,560 --> 00:44:22,020
with no ice, please.

565
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:23,160
This makes you feel fresh.

566
00:44:23,520 --> 00:44:25,940
It keeps you awake.

567
00:44:25,940 --> 00:44:26,660
I am awake.

568
00:44:27,180 --> 00:44:28,180
Otherwise, how could I be here?

569
00:44:28,880 --> 00:44:30,240
You know me.

570
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:31,060
Thank you.

571
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:37,260
You still like to complain.

572
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:39,320
How's it going, First?

573
00:44:40,040 --> 00:44:41,760
You guys went to see the client, right?

574
00:44:42,260 --> 00:44:44,560
Did Parinth have any reaction?

575
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:46,640
The client is Ms. Pailin.

576
00:44:47,260 --> 00:44:49,440
He said she's his friend from abroad.

577
00:44:49,880 --> 00:44:52,380
I remember Pailin.

578
00:44:53,280 --> 00:44:56,480
Parinth told me about her. So she's back in Thailand?

579
00:44:56,560 --> 00:44:57,120
Yes.

580
00:44:57,980 --> 00:45:01,040
She's beautiful, smart, and has a good profile.

581
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:04,620
Their ages are similar, and her company is doing well.

582
00:45:05,060 --> 00:45:06,080
I see.

583
00:45:06,340 --> 00:45:08,780
It seems like they will work together.

584
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:10,980
Mr. Parinth seems...

585
00:45:11,620 --> 00:45:12,300
What?

586
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:15,320
He seems to be impressed.

587
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:18,400
That's good news.

588
00:45:18,680 --> 00:45:20,380
What do you think, First?

589
00:45:20,760 --> 00:45:23,200
I think they are a perfect match.

590
00:45:23,340 --> 00:45:24,200
Really?

591
00:45:24,580 --> 00:45:25,440
Yes.

592
00:45:25,700 --> 00:45:26,960
I think like that.

593
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:36,380
First, tomorrow you should try asking Parinth

594
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:39,680
about his preferences in a partner.

595
00:45:41,540 --> 00:45:42,420
Deal?

596
00:45:43,280 --> 00:45:44,120
Okay.

597
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:46,400
Alright.

598
00:46:04,760 --> 00:46:05,460
Why?

599
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:07,100
What's the matter?

600
00:46:08,620 --> 00:46:09,780
Umm.

601
00:46:11,480 --> 00:46:13,320
Today is Friday.

602
00:46:13,620 --> 00:46:16,560
Don't you have any plan after work?

603
00:46:17,260 --> 00:46:17,960
No.

604
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:19,980
I usually go to the gym and then go straight home.

605
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:21,960
Is that so?

606
00:46:23,220 --> 00:46:23,660
Yes.

607
00:46:36,920 --> 00:46:38,160
I'm single.

608
00:46:39,940 --> 00:46:41,400
I don't know where to go.

609
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:45,660
Well...

610
00:46:46,180 --> 00:46:47,620
What about...

611
00:46:47,900 --> 00:46:50,260
Are you interested in anyone?

612
00:46:50,720 --> 00:46:51,920
Someone like...

613
00:46:52,120 --> 00:46:55,920
Maybe someone from the agencies or one of the clients?

614
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:57,160
No.

615
00:47:00,940 --> 00:47:02,180
Come on.

616
00:47:02,900 --> 00:47:05,060
I assumed most people would have their own preferences.

617
00:47:13,800 --> 00:47:14,520
Hey.

618
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:16,780
You want to know my type?

619
00:47:18,540 --> 00:47:19,300
Oh.

620
00:47:19,820 --> 00:47:21,080
Well...

621
00:47:21,900 --> 00:47:24,220
I want to know but...

622
00:47:24,320 --> 00:47:25,540
I like hardworking people.

623
00:47:26,140 --> 00:47:28,280
They don’t have to be excellent, but they must be diligent.

624
00:47:28,560 --> 00:47:29,780
A good heart

625
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:31,440
and have the ability to handle pressure.

626
00:47:32,620 --> 00:47:36,080
Most importantly, they should understand what I want.

627
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:37,760
They don't have to be perfect.

628
00:47:39,320 --> 00:47:40,300
They can be a bit silly.

629
00:47:40,500 --> 00:47:42,000
When they don’t know what to do,

630
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:45,000
they tend to keep pressing the pen.

631
00:47:46,140 --> 00:47:47,400
It's quite annoying.

632
00:47:47,780 --> 00:47:48,940
But, I find it funny.

633
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:55,320
Is that all?

634
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:56,040
Yes.

635
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:18,760
Are these his specs?

636
00:48:20,180 --> 00:48:21,000
Yes.

637
00:48:23,720 --> 00:48:26,340
Are you clueless or stupid?

638
00:48:28,880 --> 00:48:30,940
The person that Parinth likes

639
00:48:31,340 --> 00:48:32,540
is you.

640
00:48:36,700 --> 00:48:37,700
You're hardworking.

641
00:48:38,180 --> 00:48:39,180
You're diligent.

642
00:48:39,560 --> 00:48:40,740
You have a good heart.

643
00:48:40,800 --> 00:48:41,940
You understand him.

644
00:48:42,080 --> 00:48:43,000
You're a bit silly too.

645
00:48:43,740 --> 00:48:46,500
And also, you like to click the pen.

646
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:53,740
What he said refers to you.

647
00:48:54,060 --> 00:48:55,300
Is it not?

648
00:49:26,820 --> 00:49:28,280
I think you're drunk.

649
00:50:07,940 --> 00:50:08,800
First.

650
00:50:09,620 --> 00:50:10,380
Yes?

651
00:50:10,820 --> 00:50:12,200
Did you hear what I just said?

652
00:50:13,620 --> 00:50:14,260
Oh.

653
00:50:14,520 --> 00:50:16,400
I couldn't catch a few parts.

654
00:50:16,660 --> 00:50:17,620
Can you please say it again?

655
00:50:20,780 --> 00:50:21,880
What's wrong with you today?

656
00:50:22,700 --> 00:50:23,860
You seem distracted.

657
00:50:24,300 --> 00:50:25,240
Do you want to take a break?

658
00:50:26,880 --> 00:50:27,900
It's okay.

659
00:50:38,600 --> 00:50:39,440
Mr. Parinth.

660
00:50:43,300 --> 00:50:44,540
Well...

661
00:50:44,940 --> 00:50:47,040
I've been thinking about

662
00:50:49,620 --> 00:50:51,720
what you said yesterday.

663
00:50:52,600 --> 00:50:55,700
It might sound absurd,

664
00:50:55,700 --> 00:50:56,700
but...

665
00:50:56,980 --> 00:51:00,220
when you talked about your specs,

666
00:51:03,560 --> 00:51:05,540
you didn't mean me, right?

667
00:51:19,880 --> 00:51:20,700
First!

668
00:51:21,180 --> 00:51:22,840
Where did you get that idea from?

669
00:51:28,600 --> 00:51:33,040
I'm so sorry, Mr. Parinth. I won't talk about it again.

670
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:33,760
I was just...

671
00:51:34,760 --> 00:51:35,900
I was just imagining things.

672
00:51:39,520 --> 00:51:40,220
Er...

673
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:48,620
Hello, Pailin.

674
00:51:50,000 --> 00:51:51,100
You may leave.

675
00:51:51,500 --> 00:51:52,400
I have a meeting.

676
00:51:55,960 --> 00:51:57,260
The signal is not good.

677
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,560
Pailin! Hello, Pailin.

678
00:52:11,280 --> 00:52:12,820
Grandma, look!

679
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:21,000
Parinth! Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

680
00:52:24,560 --> 00:52:27,280
How are you? Do you feel better now?

681
00:52:27,780 --> 00:52:28,300
Hm?

682
00:52:29,740 --> 00:52:32,440
Oh! Yes! I'm much better now.

683
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:36,900
How are the meetings with all the clients going?

684
00:52:37,980 --> 00:52:39,040
Client.

685
00:52:39,900 --> 00:52:41,100
Do you mean Pailin?

686
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:43,060
You want to know about this, right?

687
00:52:44,400 --> 00:52:46,700
Or you want to know about First?

688
00:52:51,380 --> 00:52:53,780
Who? Pailin? First?

689
00:52:53,780 --> 00:52:56,940
You’ve never mentioned any of them, so how am I supposed to know?

690
00:52:58,920 --> 00:53:00,100
I know everything.

691
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:02,900
I know you sent First to keep an eye on me.

692
00:53:04,120 --> 00:53:06,340
What? What are you talking about?

693
00:53:07,780 --> 00:53:09,140
What is he talking about?

694
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:10,940
Grandma.

695
00:53:11,760 --> 00:53:12,660
You're not very convincing.

696
00:53:14,180 --> 00:53:16,840
Grandma, just tell me the truth. How did you know First?

697
00:53:19,840 --> 00:53:22,060
I met him by chance.

698
00:53:23,180 --> 00:53:23,960
Where?

699
00:53:25,360 --> 00:53:26,220
At the office.

700
00:53:26,580 --> 00:53:27,520
Then what?

701
00:53:27,780 --> 00:53:28,440
Well--

702
00:53:29,600 --> 00:53:31,940
This is getting us nowhere.

703
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:35,920
I'll tell you everything, sir.

704
00:53:37,840 --> 00:53:40,820
Madam is very worried about you.

705
00:53:40,940 --> 00:53:42,420
She followed you to the office.

706
00:53:43,320 --> 00:53:45,820
She disguised herself to keep an eye on you.

707
00:53:46,020 --> 00:53:46,880
She fainted one day.

708
00:53:48,580 --> 00:53:51,160
Luckily, Mr. First was there to help her.

709
00:53:53,020 --> 00:53:55,700
She saw that Mr. First was looking for a job.

710
00:53:56,060 --> 00:53:59,080
So she asked him to be your secretary.

711
00:54:00,100 --> 00:54:00,900
But...

712
00:54:01,320 --> 00:54:03,840
he must spy on you for her

713
00:54:03,920 --> 00:54:04,640
Hey!

714
00:54:05,420 --> 00:54:07,500
You don't have to tell him all the details,

715
00:54:07,740 --> 00:54:09,020
especially the last part.

716
00:54:10,820 --> 00:54:13,320
There's nothing left to hide, grandma.

717
00:54:13,900 --> 00:54:16,200
Your plan is no longer a secret.

718
00:54:20,220 --> 00:54:21,460
What you did was ridiculous.

719
00:54:22,820 --> 00:54:24,040
You've caused trouble for everyone.

720
00:54:24,680 --> 00:54:28,520
What trouble? First was just being my eyes and ears.

721
00:54:28,740 --> 00:54:30,560
You've caused trouble for me and First!

722
00:54:31,480 --> 00:54:33,160
Please stop bothering First.

723
00:54:36,840 --> 00:54:38,860
First didn't seem to mind.

724
00:54:40,700 --> 00:54:42,800
Also, about trying to set me up with someone and all the fuss.

725
00:54:43,460 --> 00:54:44,420
Please stop.

726
00:54:44,840 --> 00:54:46,480
There's nothing between me and First.

727
00:54:46,680 --> 00:54:47,920
We don't like each other that way.

728
00:54:48,700 --> 00:54:49,880
One more thing.

729
00:54:51,140 --> 00:54:52,860
Please stop trying to dictate my life.

730
00:54:58,520 --> 00:54:59,440
I'm leaving.

731
00:55:07,160 --> 00:55:10,480
It's okay, grandma.

732
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:11,320
Madam, it's alright.

733
00:55:11,320 --> 00:55:13,820
It's okay. Let's hug.

734
00:56:01,100 --> 00:56:01,860
Yes.

735
00:56:02,420 --> 00:56:03,020
What's up?

736
00:56:03,480 --> 00:56:04,700
Mr. Parinth.

737
00:56:05,380 --> 00:56:07,060
Your grandma is sick.

738
00:56:07,220 --> 00:56:07,820
What?

739
00:56:11,360 --> 00:56:12,100
Grandma!

740
00:56:12,100 --> 00:56:12,980
Mr. Parinth!

741
00:56:21,820 --> 00:56:22,700
How is she doing?

742
00:56:23,440 --> 00:56:25,820
Her blood sugar level suddenly dropped.

743
00:56:26,200 --> 00:56:27,360
Her blood pressure dropped too.

744
00:56:27,740 --> 00:56:29,240
She couldn't breathe properly,

745
00:56:29,360 --> 00:56:30,900
so we took her home.

746
00:56:31,260 --> 00:56:33,460
The doctor already gave her an injection.

747
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:35,480
I think she's getting better now.

748
00:56:40,740 --> 00:56:41,380
First,

749
00:56:42,420 --> 00:56:45,560
go back to the office and cancel all the appointments for today,

750
00:56:45,920 --> 00:56:47,020
and rearrange them for tomorrow instead.

751
00:56:47,420 --> 00:56:48,060
Okay.

752
00:56:50,320 --> 00:56:51,220
I...

753
00:56:52,000 --> 00:56:53,360
I'm hungry.

754
00:56:54,520 --> 00:56:57,760
I want to eat stir-fried rice noodles in gravy from Soi 33.

755
00:56:57,760 --> 00:56:59,160
My favorite restaurant.

756
00:57:00,520 --> 00:57:04,960
Will my beloved grandson go and buy it for me?

757
00:57:05,340 --> 00:57:06,400
I'll go buy it for you.

758
00:57:12,500 --> 00:57:15,040
You can go with Parinth.

759
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:16,480
Okay?

760
00:57:20,440 --> 00:57:21,140
Alright.

761
00:57:38,200 --> 00:57:41,240
Child, you're a good person.

762
00:57:41,240 --> 00:57:43,240
Thank you for helping me.

763
00:57:44,100 --> 00:57:46,680
It's okay, auntie. It's no big deal.

764
00:57:48,880 --> 00:57:50,140
Do you feel better now?

765
00:57:50,140 --> 00:57:50,760
Yes.

766
00:57:50,760 --> 00:57:51,840
Madam!

767
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:53,600
Madam!

768
00:57:55,280 --> 00:57:57,800
I told you not to do this.

769
00:58:00,760 --> 00:58:02,260
Please take a lot of rest.

770
00:58:02,920 --> 00:58:03,620
Okay.

771
00:58:05,440 --> 00:58:06,080
Mister.

772
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:12,460
You forgot this.

773
00:58:18,600 --> 00:58:19,420
Thank you.

774
00:58:21,620 --> 00:58:23,980
But I don't think I will need it anymore.

775
00:58:25,400 --> 00:58:27,400
It's too late for my job interview now.

776
00:58:32,160 --> 00:58:33,700
I will hire you.

777
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:38,060
Er...

778
00:58:39,460 --> 00:58:40,500
What did you say again?

779
00:58:41,260 --> 00:58:43,820
I will hire you to work here.

780
00:58:43,960 --> 00:58:46,640
And you will be a spy for me.

781
00:59:05,560 --> 00:59:08,380
Why don't you try to assess yourself?

782
00:59:08,720 --> 00:59:11,540
Do you think you've done well in your job?

783
00:59:15,480 --> 00:59:16,180
No.

784
00:59:20,780 --> 00:59:23,780
You can't find a perfect match for Parinth.

785
00:59:26,020 --> 00:59:28,000
I'm going to die anytime soon.

786
00:59:30,200 --> 00:59:31,320
I would like to resign.

787
00:59:37,500 --> 00:59:39,740
I'm not qualified for this job.

788
00:59:41,780 --> 00:59:43,040
Please let me resign.

789
00:59:49,380 --> 00:59:52,040
Thank you for giving me the opportunity.

790
01:00:21,580 --> 01:00:22,620
Are you leaving already?

791
01:00:27,360 --> 01:00:28,480
Want some water first?

792
01:00:33,580 --> 01:00:34,720
Thank you, Mr. Parinth,

793
01:00:37,880 --> 01:00:39,180
for everything.

794
01:00:41,780 --> 01:00:42,720
But...

795
01:00:43,680 --> 01:00:45,040
Please take care of yourself.

796
01:01:12,800 --> 01:01:13,680
Grandma.

797
01:01:14,720 --> 01:01:16,000
What did you say to First?

798
01:01:17,360 --> 01:01:19,340
Mr. Parinth, please calm down.

799
01:01:19,700 --> 01:01:21,140
I fired him.

800
01:01:25,100 --> 01:01:28,400
An employee who cannot perform the job according to the requirements

801
01:01:28,900 --> 01:01:30,160
should be fired.

802
01:01:35,240 --> 01:01:38,100
But First belongs to my team.

803
01:01:38,140 --> 01:01:38,920
Really?

804
01:01:40,560 --> 01:01:42,500
So how do you assess him?

805
01:01:43,100 --> 01:01:44,360
Tell me.

806
01:01:46,100 --> 01:01:47,740
He's good at work.

807
01:01:48,260 --> 01:01:51,220
He's determined, hardworking, and doesn't give up easily. He's also generous.

808
01:01:51,320 --> 01:01:52,280
Most importantly,

809
01:01:52,600 --> 01:01:53,920
he truly understands me.

810
01:01:54,140 --> 01:01:55,000
He is my--

811
01:01:56,860 --> 01:01:59,240
If he is so important to you,

812
01:02:00,780 --> 01:02:02,740
why are you still doing nothing.

813
01:02:04,680 --> 01:02:05,140
Hm?

814
01:02:23,560 --> 01:02:24,320
First.

815
01:02:25,780 --> 01:02:26,560
Mr. Parinth.

816
01:02:29,440 --> 01:02:31,000
Why are you waiting in front of my house?

817
01:02:35,780 --> 01:02:37,260
There's something I want to talk to you.

818
01:02:42,840 --> 01:02:43,600
Drink some water first.

819
01:02:45,400 --> 01:02:46,960
We can talk after you're not so tired.

820
01:02:49,940 --> 01:02:50,840
I'm worried.

821
01:02:57,880 --> 01:02:59,600
Why do you always say you're worried about me?

822
01:02:59,820 --> 01:03:01,300
Can you stop saying that?

823
01:03:14,820 --> 01:03:15,640
Well...

824
01:03:16,120 --> 01:03:17,520
I'm so sorry.

825
01:03:19,040 --> 01:03:20,500
The reason I get to be close to you

826
01:03:21,160 --> 01:03:24,000
is because it's part of my job.

827
01:03:25,280 --> 01:03:27,360
I got the job because of your grandmother,

828
01:03:28,600 --> 01:03:30,840
but in return, I have to take care of you.

829
01:03:31,280 --> 01:03:32,880
And report everything to her.

830
01:03:33,180 --> 01:03:34,760
Also, find me a partner.

831
01:03:38,160 --> 01:03:41,200
You knew about this?

832
01:03:42,820 --> 01:03:43,760
I knew a while ago.

833
01:03:49,320 --> 01:03:51,000
I suck at this.

834
01:03:56,640 --> 01:03:57,400
So?

835
01:03:59,640 --> 01:04:00,480
Did you succeed?

836
01:04:05,240 --> 01:04:06,680
That's the reason I quit my job.

837
01:04:10,740 --> 01:04:11,600
You quit?

838
01:04:13,700 --> 01:04:14,960
You decided to quit on your own?

839
01:04:17,600 --> 01:04:17,980
Yes.

840
01:04:19,220 --> 01:04:20,940
I just told your grandmother this afternoon.

841
01:04:24,120 --> 01:04:25,560
Gosh, grandma!

842
01:04:33,080 --> 01:04:33,700
Mr. Parinth.

843
01:04:36,800 --> 01:04:37,800
From now on,

844
01:04:38,720 --> 01:04:41,140
please don't be harsh with the new secretary.

845
01:04:42,460 --> 01:04:44,260
Don't be hot-tempered

846
01:04:45,200 --> 01:04:47,020
Everyone needs time to adjust.

847
01:04:51,340 --> 01:04:53,060
Who said I was going to change my secretary?

848
01:04:56,000 --> 01:04:58,220
But I already quit.

849
01:04:58,380 --> 01:04:59,220
I don't approve.

850
01:05:02,860 --> 01:05:04,280
What is this, Mr. Parinth?

851
01:05:04,880 --> 01:05:06,240
I'm confused.

852
01:05:17,060 --> 01:05:19,600
I want my partner to work with me.

853
01:05:23,360 --> 01:05:26,080
Mr. Parinth, why are you telling me this?

854
01:05:32,280 --> 01:05:32,760
You!

855
01:05:33,640 --> 01:05:35,160
I'm going to tell you something.

856
01:05:35,720 --> 01:05:37,340
Actually, I don’t have any specific preferences

857
01:05:37,940 --> 01:05:39,700
because I've never liked anyone first.

858
01:05:40,580 --> 01:05:41,780
But if I'm going to like someone,

859
01:05:42,980 --> 01:05:44,260
we need to be close first.

860
01:05:48,140 --> 01:05:50,600
Alright, I will tell your grandmother about this.

861
01:05:54,320 --> 01:05:56,060
Why is it so hard for you to understand?

862
01:05:59,300 --> 01:06:00,600
I like you!

863
01:06:09,940 --> 01:06:11,380
I. Like. You.

864
01:06:13,380 --> 01:06:14,480
Do you understand now?

865
01:06:22,460 --> 01:06:23,440
I understand now.

866
01:06:25,800 --> 01:06:26,940
Well...

867
01:06:28,660 --> 01:06:30,620
Why didn't you just tell me straight from the beginning?

868
01:06:33,020 --> 01:06:34,040
What about you?

869
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:36,520
How do you feel about me?

870
01:06:38,060 --> 01:06:39,300
I...

871
01:06:42,220 --> 01:06:43,600
I like you too, Mr. Parinth.

872
01:06:50,580 --> 01:06:51,380
Well then,

873
01:06:52,540 --> 01:06:54,140
how do you like me?

874
01:06:58,900 --> 01:07:00,140
I have to answer that too?

875
01:07:06,640 --> 01:07:10,840
You always say something that makes me think that you like me.

876
01:07:11,980 --> 01:07:12,960
For example...

877
01:07:14,100 --> 01:07:15,060
I'm worried about you.

878
01:07:15,880 --> 01:07:17,240
Please take care of yourself.

879
01:07:17,520 --> 01:07:20,320
I'm definitely interested if it's about you.

880
01:07:20,660 --> 01:07:21,460
Something like that.

881
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:31,960
Well...

882
01:07:34,700 --> 01:07:36,180
Can I like you as a boyfriend?

883
01:07:42,320 --> 01:07:44,000
Are you sure that's your answer?

884
01:07:47,180 --> 01:07:48,640
Have I ever lied to you?

885
01:07:57,180 --> 01:07:58,000
So...

886
01:08:00,300 --> 01:08:01,720
Will you be my boyfriend?

887
01:08:16,740 --> 01:08:17,640
Well then,

888
01:08:18,800 --> 01:08:20,340
I will use my rights as your boyfriend now.

889
01:08:22,440 --> 01:08:24,280
Mr. Parinth!

890
01:08:25,320 --> 01:08:26,000
Why?

891
01:08:27,060 --> 01:08:28,920
I'm shy!

892
01:08:28,920 --> 01:08:29,760
I can't do that?

893
01:08:30,180 --> 01:08:31,720
Mr. Parinth!

894
01:08:32,540 --> 01:08:37,860
You guys! I have the latest news!

895
01:08:38,060 --> 01:08:39,060
What is it, sis?

896
01:08:39,060 --> 01:08:40,060
Is it about our boss?

897
01:08:40,100 --> 01:08:42,160
Nope! It's about First.

898
01:08:42,340 --> 01:08:45,140
He already quit!

899
01:08:45,540 --> 01:08:46,300
Really?

900
01:08:46,300 --> 01:08:47,080
Yes.

901
01:08:47,300 --> 01:08:48,060
Why?

902
01:08:48,420 --> 01:08:50,700
I wonder too! He's really good at his work.

903
01:08:50,700 --> 01:08:51,600
Exactly.

904
01:08:51,720 --> 01:08:52,960
Where did you hear it from?

905
01:08:52,960 --> 01:08:55,140
I heard it from your team!

906
01:08:58,300 --> 01:09:00,500
Are you serious? He actually quit?

907
01:09:02,820 --> 01:09:05,080
It's false news, sis! They come to work together!

908
01:09:05,080 --> 01:09:06,200
What are you guys chatting about?

909
01:09:08,400 --> 01:09:10,560
It's nothing!

910
01:09:10,560 --> 01:09:12,100
We're just having a little chit-chat.

911
01:09:12,320 --> 01:09:13,360
Nothing much.

912
01:09:14,780 --> 01:09:17,740
If it's about First, he didn't quit his job.

913
01:09:18,180 --> 01:09:22,100
I see. That's great.

914
01:09:29,640 --> 01:09:30,720
It's more like...

915
01:09:31,800 --> 01:09:33,260
he got promoted.

916
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:36,820
Oh! Okay! He got promoted.

917
01:09:36,860 --> 01:09:41,360
He deserves it.

918
01:09:41,660 --> 01:09:43,320
We understand now, boss.

919
01:09:43,320 --> 01:09:46,520
Feel free to go ahead.

920
01:09:46,820 --> 01:09:47,960
You're welcome.

921
01:09:52,260 --> 01:09:53,340
Come here.

922
01:09:54,700 --> 01:09:56,040
Look at that.

923
01:09:57,120 --> 01:09:59,060
They're together!

924
01:09:59,060 --> 01:10:00,100
What?

925
01:10:01,660 --> 01:10:05,740
♪ How many drops of tears have I shed for love? ♪

926
01:10:05,740 --> 01:10:09,880
♪ Streaming down my face since that day ♪

927
01:10:09,880 --> 01:10:11,900
♪ It took us time to discover our love ♪

928
01:10:11,900 --> 01:10:14,520
♪ To become the dreams we unveil ♪

929
01:10:14,800 --> 01:10:16,560
♪ Never forget about this ♪

930
01:10:16,620 --> 01:10:18,300
♪ Can you do that? ♪

931
01:10:18,300 --> 01:10:21,280
♪ It’s the melody of my heart ♪

932
01:10:21,280 --> 01:10:22,280
Drink some water.

933
01:10:23,480 --> 01:10:24,480
Thank you.

934
01:10:26,720 --> 01:10:28,380
Okay, cut!

935
01:10:28,380 --> 01:10:32,080
Okay, cut! Actors, let's go over the dialogue again.

936
01:10:32,160 --> 01:10:34,240
Makeup team, please take care of their faces.

937
01:10:34,240 --> 01:10:35,500
Costume team, please check.

938
01:10:35,500 --> 01:10:37,180
Also, bring them some water.

939
01:10:57,900 --> 01:10:59,300
Please give me your son.

940
01:11:00,480 --> 01:11:02,000
I really like him.

941
01:11:02,380 --> 01:11:03,540
Auntie, please help me!

942
01:11:04,520 --> 01:11:05,980
You like vintage cars?

943
01:11:08,620 --> 01:11:11,260
Did you see the drawings on the seat?

944
01:11:12,100 --> 01:11:13,080
I did that.

945
01:11:13,960 --> 01:11:14,980
What a coincidence.

946
01:11:15,900 --> 01:11:17,580
Dad and mom must have wanted it to happen.

947
01:11:19,280 --> 01:11:20,080
Thank you

948
01:11:21,100 --> 01:11:22,560
for fixing this car for me.
